The workshop was really good. It opened a new set of options but mainly made me think in a more complex way. I would recommend to start by presenting a very simple database (CSV file) so the names of the variables during the workshop would be more familiar and simple.

First of all thank you! Your dedication to our learning is really appreciated. Nevertheless, I think the class was too big, with discrepancies between the students. That made the learning too challenging. It is possible that my expectations were too high but for that price, I expected more than what we got.

This was a great introduction to R and I am confident that I will be able to use R in the future, but I found the workshop a bit overwhelming for a beginner and I'm not sure how much I have retained. You said a lot of things were very important, but I'm not sure I'll remember them as we didn't take notes or get notes. It might have been nice if there were concrete exercises on the same dataset to try throughout the workshop in between the lectures (at least every hour) -  for example, you show us how to construct a scale, then we practice constructing a scale.

it was too fast, and too messy for people with no background at all. the choice of the study was a bit problematic because there was a lot of data and if a smaller set would have been chosen i think i would have been able to follow through more. there was also a lot of content to learn and at the end of each class it was even faster. i think it should have been with less content and slower explained. The assistant was a great help, but it was impossible to sit with her when new material was presented so overall i felt most of the time that i cannot follow. I have no programming background.
